saveWhatIfTimingModel(25.10)                      saveWhatIfTimingModel(25.10)

Name
       saveWhatIfTimingModel - Saves the specification of black boxes or black
       blobs  at the top level, including the timing arc specifications in the
       dotlib library file format

Syntax
       saveWhatIfTimingModel

       [-help]

       <blackBoxCellName>

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       Saves the specification of black boxes or black blobs at the top level,
       including the timing arc specifications in the dotlib library file for-
       mat.

       You can use this command after the module definition of a black box  or
       black blob is available with the I/O's in the Verilog netlist.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <blackBoxCellName>
              Specifies the name of the black box or black blob cell.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the file to save the information.

              Default: <BBoxName>.lib

Related Information
              * What-If Timing Analysis chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                     * Performing What-If Timing Analysis

